{
  "texts": [
    "We prove in Theorem 3.4 the numerical error of Algorithm 3.1 for solving (2.1):1 T E X * n∆t -X N n∆t ≤ O(ε) + O(∆t),with N the number of particles, ϵ the bounds of score loss, and ∆t the time step size, n∆t ≤ T. Related works:Score-based diffusion model and the error analysis.",
    "The score-based diffusion model is formulated as the forward and backward continuous Itô stochastic differential equations in [39].",
    "The score matching to train the score function by neural networks includes [20,38,15,35,14,28].",
    "For comprehensive reviews on related topics, we refer readers to [12].",
    "There are also extensive works to analyze the convergence and error estimates, for instance [10,8,7].Score-based transport modeling (SBTM) for Fokker-Planck equation."
  ]
}